1
00:00:00,170 --> 00:00:03,040
I want to quit.

2
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:05,340
Wait, already? It's only your first day!

3
00:00:05,340 --> 00:00:08,170
I'm not cut out for the corporate life.

4
00:00:08,170 --> 00:00:10,220
Huh?

5
00:00:10,590 --> 00:00:12,640
Thanks for waiting.
Here's your coffee.

6
00:00:12,640 --> 00:00:13,390
Thanks.

7
00:00:14,470 --> 00:00:16,220
It's so bitter! And so hot!

8
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:18,770
This is way too bitter.

9
00:00:18,770 --> 00:00:19,850
I'm so sorry!

10
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:21,520
Is it still printing?

11
00:00:21,520 --> 00:00:23,400
Almost done.

12
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,070
Done! Thanks for waiting.

13
00:00:25,070 --> 00:00:26,470
Thank you.

14
00:00:27,320 --> 00:00:28,650
What is this?

15
00:00:28,650 --> 00:00:29,820
The front and back are mixed up.

16
00:00:29,820 --> 00:00:31,320
I'm sorry! I'll reprint them right away.

17
00:00:32,420 --> 00:00:33,220
Oh, man.

18
00:00:37,620 --> 00:00:40,420
I'm really not cut out for this.

19
00:00:44,090 --> 00:00:46,250
Aren't you giving up a bit too quickly?

20
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:48,300
I can't do this.

21
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:49,550
You haven't even done anything yet.

22
00:00:49,550 --> 00:00:51,180
I don't think I can handle this.

23
00:00:51,180 --> 00:00:53,640
Everyone feels that way at first.

24
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:55,430
Do they?

25
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:57,020
Yeah.

26
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,980
What about you? How's school?

27
00:01:00,980 --> 00:01:03,230
Me?

28
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:05,860
Same as usual.

29
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:14,620
- Ever since my boyfriend started working,
he's grown distant.

30
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:15,830
- I totally get it.

31
00:01:15,830 --> 00:01:19,450
- He used to say things like
he wanted to be together all the time.

32
00:01:19,450 --> 00:01:23,000
Students and working adults
have such different values.

33
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,880
I get it. All those work dinners.

34
00:01:25,880 --> 00:01:28,710
They always say they have to entertain clients.

35
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:31,880
And they end up coming home so late.

36
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:34,590
I know they can't help it.

37
00:01:34,590 --> 00:01:36,180
But waiting up for them is exhausting, too.

38
00:01:36,180 --> 00:01:39,060
They act like putting work first
is just a given.

39
00:01:39,060 --> 00:01:41,430
And if you complain,
they say you're being selfish.

40
00:01:41,430 --> 00:01:43,980
I want to be understanding.

41
00:01:43,980 --> 00:01:46,690
But it feels like
I'm the only one trying.

42
00:01:46,690 --> 00:01:48,020
We're so understanding.

43
00:01:48,020 --> 00:01:50,780
Totally.

44
00:01:53,860 --> 00:01:54,990
Is everything okay?

45
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,990
It's the same as always.

46
00:01:58,990 --> 00:02:01,660
The campus is the same for the new semester.

47
00:02:01,660 --> 00:02:04,250
And I'm in the same lab.

48
00:02:04,660 --> 00:02:06,250
I see.

49
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:10,340
Must be nice. Everything's going smoothly for you,
unlike me.
